 [[2010\u201311 NFL playoffs|2010]] !! IND\n | 1 || 1 || 1 || 1 || 1.0 || 1 || 0 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n ! [[2012\u201313 NFL playoffs|2012]] !! IND\n | 1 || 1 || 9 || 114 || 12.7 || 20 || 0 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n ! [[2014\u201315 NFL playoffs|2014]] !! IND\n | 3 || 3 || 1 || 12 || 12.0 || 12 || 0 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n! colspan=2|Career\n! 21 || 21 || 93 || 1,254 || 13.5 || 72 || 9 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || 2 || 1\n|}\n\n==Post-playing career==\n[[File:ReggieWayneHonor.jpeg|thumb|Wayne in November 2018, after being inducted into the Colts' Ring of Honor.]]\nOn April 30, 2018, the Colts announced that Wayne would join the team as a volunteer receivers coach.<ref>http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000930496/article/colts-name-reggie-wayne-volunteer-receivers-coach</ref> On November 18, 2018, Wayne became the 15th player to be inducted into the team's [[Indianapolis Colts Ring of Honor|Ring of Honor]], in a ceremony attended by former teammates including Marvin Harrison, Manning and Saturday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/nfl/colts/2018/11/18/reggie-wayne-thanks-fans-colts-irsay-he-joins-ring-honor/2049251002/|title=Reggie Wayne thanks fans, Colts, Irsay as he joins Ring of Honor|website=[[IndyStar]]|date=November 18, 2018|first=Jim|last= Ayello|accessdate=November 19, 2018}}</ref> On January 2, 2020, Wayne was named one of 15 modern-era finalists for election into the Pro Football Hall of Fame in Canton, Ohio. He and [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] safety [[Troy Polamalu]] are the only two finalists for 2020 to be nominated in their first year of eligibility. The Hall of Fame selection was made on February 1, 2020, the day before Super Bowl LIV.<ref>{{cite web|title=Polamalu, Wayne lead football Hall of Fame finalists in 1st year of eligibility|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/nfl/polamalu-wayne-lead-football-hall-of-fame-finalists-in-1st-year-of-eligibility/ar-BBYyM5l?ocid=sf|access-date=January 2, 2020|website=msn.com|date=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n* [http://www.reggiewayne.com Official website]\n* [http://www.patriots.com/team/players/roster/reggie-wayne New England Patriots bio]\n* [http://www.colts.com/team/roster/Reggie-Wayne/a394623a-9a60-46b5-ad7a-4867d1c2028e Indianapolis Colts bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120312035202/http://hurricanesports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/wayne_reggie00.html Miami Hurricanes bio]\n* {{espn nfl|id=2578|name=Reggie Wayne}}\n* {{Footballstats |pfr=WaynRe00}}\n\n{{2001 NFL Draft}}\n{{ColtsFirstPick}}\n{{Super Bowl XLI}}\n{{Indianapolis Colts Ring of Honor}}\n{{NFL receiving yardage leaders}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wayne, Reggie}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:John Ehret High School alumni]]\n[[Category:African-American players of American football]]\n[[Category:American Conference Pro Bowl players]]\n[[Category:American football wide receivers]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis Colts players]]\n[[Category:Miami Hurricanes football players]]\n[[Category:New England Patriots players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from New Orleans]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl champions]]\n[[Category:People from Southwest Ranches, Florida]]\n", "name_user": "Launeywalkerbro123", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reggie_Wayne"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in France", "text_new": "{{Expand French|Pand\u00e9mie de maladie \u00e0 coronavirus de 2020 en France|date=March 2020}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in France}}\n{{Infobox outbreak\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in France\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak France per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million inhabitants by region\n| map2            = COVID-19 Outbreak Hospitalized in France 13 Regions & DomTom.svg\n| legend2         = {{center|[[Regions of France]] with number of people currently hospitalised}}\n{{legend|#FCEED3|Hospitalised 1~9}}\n{{legend|#F2A88D|Hospitalised 10~99}}\n{{legend|#E36654|Hospitalised 100~499}}\n{{legend|#E5354B|Hospitalised 500~999}}\n{{legend|#87353F|Hospitalised 1000~9999}}\n{{legend|#630606|Hospitalised \u226510000}}\n    \n| map3            =    \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = France\n| first_case      = [[Bordeaux]]\n| arrival_date    = 24 January 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=24|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China\n| recovery_cases  = 12,427<ref>{{cite web|url=https://geodes.santepubliquefrance.fr/#c=indicator&f=0&i=covid_hospit.rad&s=2020-04-02&t=a01&view=map2|title=Nombre cumul\u00e9 de personnes retourn\u00e9es \u00e0 domicile depuis le 1er mars 2020 - hommes et femmes|publisher=Sant\u00e9 Publique France|language=fr|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 5,387 (Total) <Br> 4,503 (Hospital)<ref name=\"Agence nationale de sant\u00e9 Statistics\" /> <Br> 884 ({{Interlanguage link|EHPAD|fr}})\n| confirmed_cases = 59,105<ref name=\"Agence nationale de sant\u00e9 Statistics\" />\n| website         = [https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde Public Health France]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[:France]] on 24 January 2020, when the first [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] case in Europe and France was confirmed in [[Bordeaux]]. It involved a 48-year-old French citizen who arrived in France from China. Two more cases were confirmed by the end of the day; all of the individuals had recently returned from China.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite news|last1=Jacob|first1=Etienne|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-trois-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-20200124|title=Coronavirus: trois premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en France|date=24 January 2020|work=Le Figaro|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Bernard-Stoecklin|first=S|date=13 February 2020|title=First cases of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) in France: surveillance, investigations and control measures, January 2020|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7029452/|journal=Eurosurveillance|volume=25(6)|pages=|pmc=7029452|via=PMC}}</ref> A Chinese tourist was admitted to a hospital in [[Paris]] on 28 January and died on 14 February, marking the first death from COVID-19 outside of [[Asia]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":6\" />\n\nOne key event in the spread of the disease across Metropolitan France as well as its overseas territories was the annual assembly of the [[Christian Open Door Church]] between 17 and 24 February in [[Mulhouse]] which was attended by about 2,500 people, at least half of whom are believed to have contracted the virus.<ref name=\"lepoint2369173\" /><ref name=\"francetvinfo3889133\" />\n{{As of|2020|3|31|df=UK}}, there have been 52,128 confirmed cases, 5,387 deaths within hospital and retirement homes and 7,132 recoveries in France.<ref name=\"Agence nationale de sant\u00e9 Statistics\">{{cite web|url=https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde|title=Infection au nouveau Coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2), COVID-19, France et Monde|publisher=Sant\u00e9 Publique France|language=fr|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Recoveries Minist\u00e8re de la Sant\u00e9\">{{cite press release|at=3:29|url=https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x7swzmm|language=fr|title=Point de situation coronavirus du 24 mars|trans-title=Coronavirus update on March 24|date=24 March 2020|publisher=Minist\u00e8re des Solidarit\u00e9s et de la Sant\u00e9}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, president of France [[Emmanuel Macron]] announced on public television that all schools and all universities would close from Monday 16 March until further notice.\nThe next day, the prime minister [[\u00c9douard Philippe]] banned gatherings of more than 100 people, not including public transportation.  The following day, the prime minister ordered the closure of all nonessential public places, including restaurants, caf\u00e9s, cinemas, and discoth\u00e8ques, effective at midnight.<ref name=\"bbc51892477\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477|title=Coronavirus: Spain and France announce sweeping restrictions|work=BBC News|date=15 March 2020|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref> On 16 March, [[President Macron]] announced a national lockdown for 15 days starting on 17 March midday. On 27 March, Prime Minister \u00c9douard Philippe announced that the lockdown would be extended until 15 April.<ref name=\"independent9405136\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-france-lockdown-cases-update-covid-19-macron-a9405136.html|title=France imposes 15-day lockdown as part of emergency coronavirus response|date=16 March 2020|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/France medical cases chart}}\n\n===First confirmed cases===\nOn 24 January, the first COVID-19 case in Europe was confirmed in [[Bordeaux]]. A 48-year-old French citizen from China, who arrived in France on 22 January, was hospitalised at Centre Hospitalier Universitaire de Bordeaux. [[Service d'Aide M\u00e9dicale Urgente]] took charge and the patient was isolated in the hospital. The authorities tried to confirm whether he had infected people who were in contact with him.<ref name=\"francetvinfo3799837\">{{cite news|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/coronavirus-en-france-le-parcours-des-trois-patients_3799837.html|title=Coronavirus en France : le parcours des trois patients|date=24 January 2020|work=France Info|access-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221231826/https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/coronavirus-en-france-le-parcours-des-trois-patients_3799837.html|archive-date=21 February 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nTwo more cases were confirmed in Paris by the end of the day \u2013 a couple who had returned from China on 18 January.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-outbreak-hospital-to-be-built-in-five-days-as-death-toll-rises-in-china-11916211|title=Coronavirus outbreak: First confirmed cases in Europe as France declares two infections|publisher=Sky News|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"lemonde6027158\">{{cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/01/24/coronavirus-deux-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-a-bordeaux-et-paris_6027158_3244.html|title=Coronavirus : deux premi\u00e8res contaminations confirm\u00e9es en France|date=24 January 2020|work=Le Monde|access-date=24 January 2020|language=fr}}</ref> The 31-year-old man and his 30-year-old partner, both from [[Wuhan]], tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and were hospitalised at [[Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital]] in Paris.\n\nOn 28 January, an 80-year-old Chinese tourist from Hubei tested positive and was hospitalised at Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital,<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/france-confirms-fourth-case-of-coronavirus-in-elderly-chinese-tourist|title=Wuhan virus: France confirms fourth case of coronavirus in elderly Chinese tourist|date=29 January 2020|website=The Straits Times|access-date=26 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220191811/https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/france-confirms-fourth-case-of-coronavirus-in-elderly-chinese-tourist|archive-date=20 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> the following day, his 50-year-old daughter tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital.<ref name=\"lexpress2116745\">{{cite web |title=Cinqui\u00e8me case aver\u00e9 |url=https://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/sante/coronavirus-un-cinquieme-cas-avere-en-france-la-fille-du-quatrieme-malade_2116745.html |website=L'Express |accessdate=29 January 2020 |date=29 January 2020 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129193013/https://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/sante/coronavirus-un-cinquieme-cas-avere-en-france-la-fille-du-quatrieme-malade_2116745.html |archive-date=29 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The 80-year-old Chinese tourist died on 14 February, marking the first death from COVID-19 in outside of Asia.<ref name=\":6\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837|title=First coronavirus death confirmed in Europe|date=15 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219204410/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837|archive-date=19 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 January, a Paris doctor who had come into contact with a Chinese tourist whose infection was confirmed upon her return to China was confirmed positive for COVID-19.<ref name=\"leparisien8248956\">{{cite web|title=Coronavirus: un sixi\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/coronavirus-un-sixieme-cas-confirme-en-france-un-medecin-confine-a-paris-30-01-2020-8248956.php|website=Le Parisien|accessdate=30 January 2020|date=30 January 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131112945/http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/coronavirus-un-sixieme-cas-confirme-en-france-un-medecin-confine-a-paris-30-01-2020-8248956.php|archive-date=31 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\" style=\"margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;\"\n|-\n!Case\n!Date\n!Age\n!Gender\n!Nationality\n!Hospital admitted to\n!Source of infection\n!Status\n!Note\n!Source\n|-\n|1\n| rowspan=\"3\" |24 January 2020\n|48\n|Male\n|French\n|H\u00f4pital Pellegrin, [[Bordeaux]]\n|rowspan=\"5\" |China\n|Discharged\n|First case in Europe. Wine merchant back from China. Out of hospital on 13 February.\n|<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux|title=Coronavirus : Que sait-on du cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Bordeaux ?|last=Provenzano|first=Elsa|date=26 January 2020|work=20 Minutes|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219143036/https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux|archive-date=19 February 2020|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/epidemie-de-coronavirus-le-premier-malade-diagnostique-en-france-affirme-etre-sorti-de-l-hopital_3824827.html|title=Epid\u00e9mie de coronavirus : le premier malade diagnostiqu\u00e9 en France affirme \u00eatre gu\u00e9ri et sorti de l'h\u00f4pital|date=13 February 2020|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215004230/https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/epidemie-de-coronavirus-le-premier-malade-diagnostique