-20/blues-albums \"Blues Albums: September 20, 2014\"], ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''. Retrieved August 10, 2015.</ref>\n<ref name=BillboardIndependent>[http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-09-20/independent-albums \"Independent Albums: September 20, 2014\"], ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''. Retrieved August 16, 2015.</ref>\n<ref name=MCA>Mehr, Bob. [http://www.commercialappeal.com/go-memphis/music/news/bishop-rush-among-blues-music-award-winners_95761929 \"Bishop, Rush Among Blues Music Award Winners\"], ''[[The Commercial Appeal]]''. Retrieved August 16, 2015.</ref>\n<ref name=NYBluesHallOfFame>[http://www.blueshalloffame.com/Local_Blues_Talent/Local_Blues_Talent_of_New_York.html#Paul_Nelson \"Paul  Nelson\"], New York Blues Hall of Fame. Retrieved August 11, 2015.</ref>\n<ref name=BluesFoundation>[http://www.blueswebzine.com/news/0022.html \"Keeping the Blues Alive Award Recipients Announced\"], BluesWebzine.com, November 15, 2010. Retrieved August 11, 2015.</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|paulnelsonguitar.com}}\n*[http://somedayprods.com/talking/pillow-talkings-interview-with-paul-nelson/ Pillow Talking's Interview with Paul Nelson]\n*[https://www.vintageguitar.com/18117/paul-nelson/ Paul Nelson - Main Man to the Blues Man], Vintage Guitar\n*[http://www.namm.org/library/oral-history/paul-nelson Paul Nelson interview] - NAMM Oral History Library (2017)\n{{Johnny Winter}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nelson, Paul}}\n[[Category:American guitarists]]\n[[Category:American record producers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:JT Taylor\u2192James \"J.T.\" Taylor,Harvey Brooks\u2192Harvey Brooks (bassist),George Lynch\u2192George Lynch (musician)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Nelson_(musician)"}
